{
  "enabled": true,
  "name": "Interface Step 3: Execute Tests in FSM",
  "description": "Step 3: Execute test scenarios using the automated testing framework",
  "version": "2.0.0",
  "when": {
    "type": "userTriggered"
  },
  "then": {
    "type": "askAgent",
    "prompt": "Execute Step 3: Execute Interface Tests Using Framework\n\nYou are executing interface tests using the FSM automation framework.\n\n**STEP 1: USER SELECTION (Interactive)**\n1. List clients in Projects/ → User selects client\n2. List test scenario JSON files in Projects/{ClientName}/TestScripts/ → User selects scenario\n   - Look in inbound/, outbound/, or approval/ subfolders\n   - Look for *_test.json files\n   - Example: INT_FIN_013_inbound_test.json\n\n**STEP 2: VERIFY PREREQUISITES**\n3. Verify credentials exist:\n   - Projects/{ClientName}/Credentials/.env.fsm\n   - Projects/{ClientName}/Credentials/.env.passwords\n4. For inbound tests, verify SFTP credentials in .env.passwords\n5. Read the selected JSON file to show scenario summary:\n   - Interface ID\n   - Interface type (inbound/outbound/approval)\n   - Number of scenarios\n   - Scenario titles\n6. Confirm with user: \"Ready to execute {X} scenarios for {interface_id}?\"\n\n**STEP 3: EXECUTE FRAMEWORK**\n7. Execute the testing framework directly in Kiro context:\n\n```python\nimport sys\nfrom pathlib import Path\nsys.path.insert(0, 'ReusableTools')\n\nfrom testing_framework.orchestration.test_orchestrator import TestOrchestrator\nfrom testing_framework.utils.logger import Logger\n\n# Initialize logger\nlogger = Logger('interface_test', verbose=True)\n\n# Initialize orchestrator\norchestrator = TestOrchestrator(\n    client_name='{ClientName}',\n    environment='{ClientName}',  # Use client name as environment\n    logger=logger\n)\n\n# Run the test\ntry:\n    result = orchestrator.run('Projects/{ClientName}/TestScripts/{type}/{scenario_file}')\n    \n    # Show results\n    print(f'\\\\n=== TEST EXECUTION COMPLETE ===')\n    print(f'Interface: {result.interface_id}')\n    print(f'Type: {result.interface_type}')\n    print(f'Status: {\"PASSED\" if result.passed else \"FAILED\"}')\n    print(f'Scenarios Executed: {len(result.scenario_results)}')\n    \n    # Show per-scenario results\n    for scenario_result in result.scenario_results:\n        status_icon = '✅' if scenario_result.passed else '❌'\n        print(f'{status_icon} Scenario {scenario_result.scenario_id}: {scenario_result.title}')\n    \n    if hasattr(result, 'tes070_path') and result.tes070_path:\n        print(f'\\\\nTES-070 Document: {result.tes070_path}')\n    \nfinally:\n    orchestrator.cleanup()\n```\n\n8. The framework will automatically:\n   - Initialize unique run_group identifier (AUTOTEST_YYYYMMDDHHMMSS_RANDOM)\n   - Load credentials from .env files\n   - Execute each scenario sequentially:\n     \n     **For Inbound:**\n     * Upload test file to SFTP\n     * Wait for File Channel trigger (adaptive polling)\n     * Monitor work unit completion\n     * Validate data imported to FSM\n     * Capture screenshots at each step\n     \n     **For Outbound:**\n     * Trigger IPA manually or via schedule\n     * Monitor work unit completion\n     * Download output file from SFTP\n     * Validate output file content\n     * Capture screenshots at each step\n     \n     **For Approval:**\n     * Login to FSM\n     * Create transaction (invoice/journal/etc)\n     * Submit for approval\n     * Monitor work unit completion\n     * Verify final status\n     * Capture screenshots at each step\n   \n   - Save evidence to Projects/{ClientName}/Temp/evidence/{scenario_id}/\n   - Generate TES-070 document automatically\n   - Close browser and cleanup resources\n\n**STEP 4: SHOW RESULTS**\n9. Display execution summary:\n   - Total scenarios: {X}\n   - Passed: {Y}\n   - Failed: {Z}\n   - Evidence location: Projects/{ClientName}/Temp/evidence/\n   - TES-070 location: Projects/{ClientName}/TES-070/Generated_TES070s/\n\n10. If any scenarios failed:\n    - List failed scenarios with scenario IDs\n    - Show evidence paths for debugging\n    - Suggest reviewing screenshots in evidence folders\n\n11. Next steps:\n    - ✅ Step 3 complete!\n    - 📄 TES-070 document already generated by framework\n    - 📝 Open document at: Projects/{ClientName}/TES-070/Generated_TES070s/\n    - 🔄 Press F9 in Word to update Table of Contents\n    - 🔍 Review screenshots and results\n    - ✨ Testing complete!\n\n**CRITICAL FRAMEWORK NOTES:**\n- Framework MUST run in Kiro's execution context (MCP tools only available here)\n- Do NOT try to run as subprocess: `python run_tests.py` will fail\n- Execute the Python code directly as shown above\n- Framework handles all Playwright MCP calls internally\n- Framework handles all SFTP operations internally\n- State management with {{state.variable}} interpolation automatic\n- Evidence collection and TES-070 generation automatic\n- Browser stays open across scenarios for efficiency\n\n**WHAT THE FRAMEWORK DOES AUTOMATICALLY:**\n\n**Inbound Interface:**\n1. **SFTP Upload** - Upload test file to SFTP server\n2. **Wait for Trigger** - Monitor for File Channel trigger (adaptive polling)\n3. **Monitor Work Unit** - Wait for IPA completion\n4. **Validate Data** - Query FSM to verify data imported\n5. **Screenshots** - Capture evidence at each step\n\n**Outbound Interface:**\n1. **Trigger IPA** - Start IPA execution (manual or scheduled)\n2. **Monitor Work Unit** - Wait for IPA completion\n3. **SFTP Download** - Download output file from SFTP\n4. **Validate File** - Verify file content matches expected\n5. **Screenshots** - Capture evidence at each step\n\n**Approval Interface:**\n1. **Login** - Navigate to FSM portal, authenticate\n2. **Navigate** - Open application, expand sidebar\n3. **Create Transaction** - Fill form, create distribution, save\n4. **Submit** - Click Submit for Approval, verify status\n5. **Monitor** - Navigate to Work Units, wait for completion\n6. **Verify** - Check final status matches expected\n7. **Screenshots** - Capture evidence at each step\n\n**EXECUTION FLOW:**\n1. User selects client and scenario file\n2. Kiro loads framework code\n3. Kiro executes framework in its context\n4. Framework calls Playwright MCP tools (available in Kiro context)\n5. Framework calls SFTP operations (for inbound/outbound)\n6. All scenarios execute automatically\n7. Evidence captured, TES-070 generated\n8. Results displayed to user\n\n**ERROR HANDLING:**\n- If credentials missing: Show error, guide user to add credentials\n- If scenario file invalid: Show validation errors\n- If execution fails: Show error, mark scenario as FAILED, continue to next\n- If browser issues: Show error, attempt recovery, continue if possible\n- If SFTP issues: Show error, mark scenario as FAILED, continue\n- All errors logged to console for debugging\n\n**FRAMEWORK ADVANTAGES:**\n- Token efficient (framework automates all steps)\n- Consistent execution (same logic every time)\n- Automatic evidence collection (screenshots, state tracking)\n- Built-in TES-070 generation (no separate step needed)\n- Adaptive polling (smart wait times for work units)\n- State interpolation ({{state.run_group}} in configs)\n- Error resilience (continues on failure)\n- Supports all interface types (inbound, outbound, approval)\n\n**INTERFACE-SPECIFIC NOTES:**\n\n**Inbound:**\n- Framework uploads ONE file at a time (sequential execution)\n- Waits for File Channel trigger (adaptive polling: 10s → 30s → 60s)\n- Validates data in FSM via API or UI\n- Captures SFTP upload evidence\n\n**Outbound:**\n- Framework triggers IPA execution\n- Monitors work unit completion\n- Downloads output file from SFTP\n- Validates file content\n- Captures SFTP download evidence\n\n**Approval:**\n- Framework creates transactions with unique IDs\n- Submits for approval workflow\n- Monitors work unit completion\n- Verifies final status matches expected\n- Captures FSM UI evidence\n\nAfter completion, tell the user: 'Step 3 complete. {passed}/{total} scenarios passed. TES-070 document generated at: {tes070_path}. Open in Word and press F9 to update Table of Contents. Interface testing complete!'"
  }
}
